=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_SetResetFF_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A neutral mixed sound, with saw_like oscillator character around 50 Hz, featuring slow attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally sparse.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: slow
  brightness: neutral
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: very_dynamic
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: mixed
  spectral_complexity_mean: sparse
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 50.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: -1.4677
  harmonic_regularity: 0.9613
  pitch_clarity: 8.4699
  inharmonicity: 0.0296
  type: saw_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -9.4088
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: SetResetFF Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/SetResetFF.html
// Tags: SetResetFF, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
(
play({
    a = Dust.ar(5); // the set trigger
    b = Dust.ar(5); // the reset trigger
    SetResetFF.ar(a, b) * BrownNoise.ar(0.2);

}))
